2,/Hotel_Review-g186338-d254574-Reviews-or0-King_Solomon_Hotel-London_England.html#REVIEWS,"King Solomon Hotel Reviews, London",Surprisingly Good,"I stayed here just for 1 night. The hotel is located on a main road that leads to a High Street shopping area mainly of Jewish influence. A small reception with easy check in, sits in front of the narrow stairs that lead up to narrow, lino corridors so although it was hard to bring a case up the stairs, it was easy to pull a suitcase to the rooms. As you walked in the room there was a wardrobe with a safe in it. Then there was a double drawer desk with stool,  a mirror above and a wall mounted hair dryer next to it. Under the window was a coffee table with tea/coffee facilities and 2 armchairs. The double bed was nicely dressed with turquoise cushions and a bed runner and with 3 drawer bedside tables on either side. There was also a small wall mounted, flat-screen TV. The bathroom  has no bath but a double shower with a single sink, a mirror above and basic toiletries. There was a lounge area which looks trendy because of the colourful settees and padded stools with scattered patterned cushions, artistic pictures,  coffee tables and a bar/mini shop. The breakfast area looks uniform as rectangle tables are set for 4 in rows either side of round tables also set for 4. The food was adequate but seemed to have more cold food than hot and some foods I didn't not recognise so  I had to guess what I had taken to eat.  There was also a small, free, front drive car park in front of the hotel's reception and an outside garden area at the back with additional seating. Overall a well kept hotel with some pretty features.‚Ä¶",Date of stay: December 2019,4.0
